  "prompt": "What is meaning of impeachment?",
  "response": "Impeachment is a formal process in which an official is accused of unlawful activity, including betrayal of public trust, mismanagement, and violations of law. In the context of government, it is usually the first step towards the removal of a public official from office. The process typically involves several stages, including:\n\n1. Investigation and evidence-gathering.\n2. Approval of articles of impeachment (formal charges) by a legislative body, often the lower house.\n3. Trial and deliberation by the upper house or another designated body, which determines whether the accused should be removed from office.\n\nImpeachment does not necessarily result in the removal from office; rather, it signifies that charges have been brought against the official. The subsequent trial determines the outcome based on the evidence presented.",
